flowRoot.flowPara: Including more actions - rows expand (applies to popovers and dialogs)
Container types - popover, dialog (full width list), dialog (embedded)
Add button becomes sensitive when the entry field contains a valid entry.
Inline undo button is shown for 4/5 seconds.
Only possible for lists in windows.
Remove button is replaced with a dropdown when renaming is required.
Rows become insensitive when rename is active. Action bar transforms to show cancel and rename buttons (rename becomes sensitive when changes have been made).
Handles allow each row to be dragged.

New list widget can be placed at the bottom or the top, depending on where new rows are inserted into the list. An action bar can also be used in the embedded list case (if the list is anticipated to be long, for example).
